WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.170 align:middle line:90%


00:00:02.170 --> 00:00:05.260 align:middle line:90%


00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:39.290 align:middle line:90%
WHERE I'VE COME TO

00:00:39.290 --> 00:00:43.080 align:middle line:90%
AND PLACES I'M GOING...

00:00:45.960 --> 00:00:47.460 align:middle line:90%
SLOW DOWN. ALEX.

00:00:47.460 --> 00:00:48.590 align:middle line:84%
YOU CAN GO A LITTLE
FASTER THAN THIS.

00:00:48.590 --> 00:00:53.090 align:middle line:84%
WE'RE RUNNING
OFF THE PATH HERE.

00:00:53.090 --> 00:00:56.930 align:middle line:90%


00:01:02.650 --> 00:01:04.110 align:middle line:90%
HEY!

00:01:07.440 --> 00:01:09.570 align:middle line:90%
HEY!

00:01:10.570 --> 00:01:15.120 align:middle line:90%


00:01:15.120 --> 00:01:19.120 align:middle line:84%
I TRY TO SEE IT CLEAR
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHY IT'S HERE

00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:20.660 align:middle line:90%
WHAT'S COMING UP AHEAD?

00:01:20.660 --> 00:01:24.330 align:middle line:84%
A SLIGHT DECLINE,
THANK GOD.

00:01:24.330 --> 00:01:26.500 align:middle line:90%
RIGHT TURN, 2:00.

00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:28.170 align:middle line:84%
WE NEED
TO GO FASTER,

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:30.010 align:middle line:84%
OR ELSE LEARN
TO RUN ON GRASS.

00:01:30.010 --> 00:01:30.420 align:middle line:84%
[BREATHLESSLY]
I THINK I NEED TO STOP.

00:01:30.420 --> 00:01:32.759 align:middle line:90%
[WINCING IN PAIN]

00:01:39.020 --> 00:01:47.520 align:middle line:84%
...WHERE I'M WISER
AND GROWING TALLER

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:50.360 align:middle line:90%
I WILL SEE THE WAY...

00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:51.780 align:middle line:90%
ALEX!

00:01:53.660 --> 00:01:54.740 align:middle line:90%
ALEX!

00:02:03.540 --> 00:02:07.130 align:middle line:90%


00:02:12.420 --> 00:02:16.260 align:middle line:90%
GO AHEAD, SHOOT HIM!

00:02:16.260 --> 00:02:17.510 align:middle line:90%
I WON'T TELL ANYONE.

00:02:17.510 --> 00:02:18.510 align:middle line:90%
YOU OKAY, TIGER?

00:02:18.510 --> 00:02:19.430 align:middle line:90%
I'M ALL RIGHT.

00:02:19.430 --> 00:02:22.020 align:middle line:90%
[WINCING IN PAIN]

00:02:23.640 --> 00:02:24.850 align:middle line:90%
HERE, LET ME SEE.

00:02:28.060 --> 00:02:31.530 align:middle line:84%
THAT'S ALL RIGHT,
IT'S NOT SO BAD.

00:02:31.530 --> 00:02:33.360 align:middle line:90%
[BREATHING HARD]

00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:35.200 align:middle line:84%
THANK GOD YOUR MOTHER
IS ALREADY AT WORK.

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:36.280 align:middle line:90%
SHE'D FREAK OUT.

00:02:36.280 --> 00:02:37.570 align:middle line:90%
PLEASE DON'T TELL HER.

00:02:37.570 --> 00:02:41.490 align:middle line:84%
YOU THINK I WANT TO
SLEEP IN THE TOOL SHED.

00:02:41.490 --> 00:02:43.370 align:middle line:90%
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

00:02:43.370 --> 00:02:46.460 align:middle line:90%
YOU KNOW OUR RULES.

00:02:46.460 --> 00:02:48.840 align:middle line:90%
I KNOW, DAD, I JUST...

00:02:48.840 --> 00:02:50.590 align:middle line:84%
I WANTED TO RUN FOR ONCE
WITHOUT BEING HELD BACK,

00:02:50.590 --> 00:02:52.630 align:middle line:90%
YOU KNOW?

00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:54.380 align:middle line:90%
HELD BACK.

00:02:56.180 --> 00:02:58.550 align:middle line:90%
[SNACK PACKAGE CRINKLES]

00:02:58.550 --> 00:03:00.180 align:middle line:90%
[GROANS, WINCING]

00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:03.680 align:middle line:84%
YOU MIGHT BE A LITTLE FASTER
IF YOU DIDN'T EAT SO MUCH.

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:05.140 align:middle line:90%
HOW'S THAT?

00:03:05.140 --> 00:03:07.270 align:middle line:90%
AREN'T YOU ON A DIET?

00:03:07.270 --> 00:03:09.440 align:middle line:84%
IT'S GRANOLA.
IT DOESN'T COUNT.

00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:11.570 align:middle line:90%
SURE.

00:03:11.570 --> 00:03:14.240 align:middle line:84%
BY THE WAY, I HAPPEN TO BE
40-BLAH-BLAH YEARS OLD,

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:16.450 align:middle line:90%
AND I WASN'T A FAST RUNNER EVER.

00:03:16.450 --> 00:03:17.450 align:middle line:84%
YOU, ON THE OTHER HAND,
HAVE BECOME VERY FAST.

00:03:17.450 --> 00:03:19.280 align:middle line:90%
YOU'RE--

00:03:19.280 --> 00:03:20.829 align:middle line:90%
FASTER THAN A SPEEDING BULLET?

00:03:20.829 --> 00:03:23.120 align:middle line:84%
NOT ABLE TO LEAP TRASH CANS
IN A SINGLE BOUND?

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:27.170 align:middle line:84%
FASTER THAN A WHEEZING
PROBATION OFFICER ANYHOW.

00:03:27.170 --> 00:03:28.750 align:middle line:90%
HEY, DID YOU TALK TO MS. McVIE

00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:30.170 align:middle line:84%
ABOUT JOINING
THE CROSS COUNTRY TEAM?

00:03:30.170 --> 00:03:32.210 align:middle line:84%
I'LL HAVE TO TALK
TO HER AGAIN.

00:03:32.210 --> 00:03:36.470 align:middle line:84%
DON'T WORRY,
YOU'RE GOING TO MAKE THAT TEAM.

00:03:37.470 --> 00:03:41.180 align:middle line:84%
DAD, I AM SORRY ABOUT
TAKING OFF ON YOU LIKE THAT.

00:03:41.180 --> 00:03:43.220 align:middle line:90%
[SIGHS IN DISAPPOINTMENT]

00:03:43.220 --> 00:03:44.600 align:middle line:84%
WE GOT TO GO, BUDDY.
[WINCING]

00:03:44.600 --> 00:03:46.520 align:middle line:90%
SOMEBODY'S IN TROUBLE.

00:03:52.520 --> 00:03:55.490 align:middle line:90%
WELL, I'M NOT STICKING AROUND.

00:03:55.490 --> 00:03:59.110 align:middle line:84%
I'M NOT TALKING
TO NO JUDGE ABOUT NOTHING.

00:03:59.110 --> 00:04:01.240 align:middle line:84%
I'M TIRED
OF LOOKING LIKE A FOOL,

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:04.410 align:middle line:84%
BAILING YOU OUT,
LYING TO PEOPLE,

00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:05.580 align:middle line:90%
"OH, HE'LL NEVER DO IT AGAIN.

00:04:05.580 --> 00:04:08.290 align:middle line:90%
OH, THIS IS THE LAST TIME."

00:04:10.170 --> 00:04:12.420 align:middle line:84%
YOU CAN DEAL WITH
WHATEVER THEY THROW AT YOU!

00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:18.720 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW, IF I COULD FIND HER,
I'D SEND YOU TO YOUR MOTHER'S,

00:04:18.720 --> 00:04:22.140 align:middle line:90%
IF SHE WANTED YOU.

00:04:22.140 --> 00:04:23.350 align:middle line:90%
[SIGHS IN EXASPERATION]

00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:51.540 align:middle line:84%
WATCH MITCH!
WATCH MITCH! WATCH MITCH!

00:04:52.580 --> 00:04:53.840 align:middle line:90%
YUP, YUP, YUP!

00:04:57.210 --> 00:04:59.380 align:middle line:90%
HELLO, JULIE.

00:04:59.380 --> 00:05:00.170 align:middle line:90%
[GIGGLES]

00:05:00.170 --> 00:05:01.840 align:middle line:84%
I WISH YOU
WOULDN'T DO THAT.

00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:02.720 align:middle line:84%
HOW DO YOU ALWAYS
KNOW IT'S ME?

00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:04.260 align:middle line:84%
BECAUSE NOBODY ELSE
AT THIS SCHOOL

00:05:04.260 --> 00:05:06.850 align:middle line:84%
HAS THE PERFUME I GOT YOU
FOR A CHRISTMAS PRESENT.

00:05:06.850 --> 00:05:08.810 align:middle line:84%
IT WAS MY CLEVER WAY
OF IDENTIFYING YOU.

00:05:08.810 --> 00:05:10.270 align:middle line:84%
WELL, I'M GLAD YOU DON'T
MARK YOUR TERRITORY

00:05:10.270 --> 00:05:10.730 align:middle line:90%
LIKE A DOG.

00:05:10.730 --> 00:05:13.400 align:middle line:90%
NAVIGATION UPDATE,

00:05:13.400 --> 00:05:13.900 align:middle line:84%
THE ART DEPARTMENT
HAS A DISPLAY

00:05:13.900 --> 00:05:15.520 align:middle line:90%
ON THE SECOND FLOOR,

00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:16.570 align:middle line:84%
AND THEY'VE
BEEN WAXING--

00:05:16.570 --> 00:05:17.730 align:middle line:84%
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
THAT'S TRAVELLING, DUDE!

00:05:17.730 --> 00:05:19.570 align:middle line:84%
THAT WAS TWO STEPS, MITCH,
JUST TWO STEPS.

00:05:19.570 --> 00:05:20.650 align:middle line:84%
YEAH, MORE LIKE
FIVE, TYSON.

00:05:20.650 --> 00:05:22.570 align:middle line:84%
IS THAT TYSON BRIDEAU
ARGUING OVER THERE?

00:05:22.570 --> 00:05:24.570 align:middle line:84%
YEAH, THAT'S THE PRINCE
OF JOCK STRAPS FOR SURE.

00:05:24.570 --> 00:05:26.200 align:middle line:90%
I GUESS HE'S STILL

00:05:26.200 --> 00:05:27.370 align:middle line:84%
ON THE CROSS COUNTRY
TEAM THIS YEAR?

00:05:27.370 --> 00:05:29.450 align:middle line:84%
SEEING AS HE BROKE ANOTHER
COUNTY RECORD LAST YEAR,

00:05:29.450 --> 00:05:30.410 align:middle line:90%
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

00:05:30.410 --> 00:05:32.420 align:middle line:84%
LET ME GUESS,
HE'S ON THE TEAM.

00:05:32.420 --> 00:05:32.920 align:middle line:84%
ADMIT IT, TYSON,
YOU TRAVELLED.

00:05:32.920 --> 00:05:34.830 align:middle line:90%
ARE YOU SERIOUS, MAN?

00:05:34.830 --> 00:05:36.710 align:middle line:90%
SERIOUSLY!

00:05:36.710 --> 00:05:39.300 align:middle line:84%
IT WAS TWO STEPS, MAN,
YOU'RE ALL FREAKIN' TRIPPING!

00:05:39.300 --> 00:05:40.050 align:middle line:90%
YOU'RE BLIND, MAN!

00:05:41.670 --> 00:05:43.220 align:middle line:90%
NO OFFENCE THERE, ALAN.

00:05:43.220 --> 00:05:45.470 align:middle line:90%
NO OFFENCE TAKEN, TYSON.

00:05:45.470 --> 00:05:46.760 align:middle line:90%
IT'S ALEX, BY THE WAY.

00:05:46.760 --> 00:05:47.810 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS AWKWARDLY]

00:05:47.810 --> 00:05:50.430 align:middle line:90%
WHAT A SWEETHEART.

00:05:50.430 --> 00:05:52.520 align:middle line:84%
AT LEAST HE GOT THE FIRST
LETTER OF YOUR NAME RIGHT,

00:05:52.520 --> 00:05:53.060 align:middle line:90%
THINGS ARE IMPROVING.

00:05:53.060 --> 00:05:55.100 align:middle line:90%
YEAH, THAT MEANS A LOT.

00:05:55.100 --> 00:05:56.770 align:middle line:84%
JULIE, IS EVERYONE
JUST STANDING THERE,

00:05:56.770 --> 00:05:58.360 align:middle line:90%
AWKWARDLY STARING AT ME

00:05:58.360 --> 00:06:00.400 align:middle line:90%
WITH THEIR MOUTHS OPEN?

00:06:00.400 --> 00:06:00.900 align:middle line:90%
YEAH.

00:06:00.900 --> 00:06:02.820 align:middle line:90%
WE SHOULD PROBABLY GO

00:06:02.820 --> 00:06:04.410 align:middle line:84%
BEFORE THEY LET ALL
THE AIR OUT OF THEIR HEADS.

00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:05.910 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHING]
ALL RIGHT.

00:06:11.950 --> 00:06:13.710 align:middle line:90%
HIYA, BRAD.

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:21.920 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW, I HAVE
A LOT OF ADULT PAROLEES

00:06:21.920 --> 00:06:25.260 align:middle line:84%
WHOSE LIVES WOULD MAKE
MOVIES OF THE WEEK,

00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:29.470 align:middle line:84%
AND THEIR FILES AREN'T
HALF AS THICK AS YOURS.

00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:33.480 align:middle line:84%
A LOT OF PEOPLE HAVE STUCK
THEIR NECKS OUT FOR YOU, BRAD,

00:06:33.480 --> 00:06:35.100 align:middle line:90%
INCLUDING MYSELF.

00:06:35.100 --> 00:06:39.730 align:middle line:84%
ALL YOU'VE DONE
IS BLOW EVERY OPPORTUNITY.

00:06:41.480 --> 00:06:42.400 align:middle line:90%
[SLAPS TABLETOP]

00:06:42.400 --> 00:06:43.860 align:middle line:84%
WHY DON'T YOU
COME WITH ME?

00:06:52.790 --> 00:06:54.100 align:middle line:84%
THIS LATEST EPISODE
WAS JUST SO...

00:06:54.100 --> 00:06:57.040 align:middle line:90%
STUPID? IDIOTIC? OBTUSE?

00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:58.130 align:middle line:90%
OH, FUNNY STUFF.

00:06:58.130 --> 00:07:00.000 align:middle line:84%
YOU MIGHT WANT TO SAVE
YOUR "A" MATERIAL

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:01.840 align:middle line:84%
FOR JUDGE MELANSON
TOMORROW.

00:07:01.840 --> 00:07:03.970 align:middle line:90%
HE LOVES TO LAUGH.

00:07:03.970 --> 00:07:06.930 align:middle line:84%
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU BROKE PROBATION.

00:07:06.930 --> 00:07:10.430 align:middle line:84%
I THOUGHT WE WERE
MAKING PROGRESS.

00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:12.010 align:middle line:84%
ROBBING A BEAUTY SALON
IN BROAD DAYLIGHT?

00:07:12.010 --> 00:07:13.850 align:middle line:90%
THAT DOESN'T SOUND LIKE YOU.

00:07:13.850 --> 00:07:15.810 align:middle line:90%
THAT KIND OF STUPIDITY

00:07:15.810 --> 00:07:17.650 align:middle line:84%
HAS THE BERNARD BROTHERS
WRITTEN ALL OVER IT.

00:07:17.650 --> 00:07:19.690 align:middle line:84%
LOOK, THEY HAVE
NOTHING TO DO WITH IT.

00:07:19.690 --> 00:07:21.480 align:middle line:84%
LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING,

00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:22.900 align:middle line:90%
LOYALTY AND GULLIBILITY,

00:07:22.900 --> 00:07:25.780 align:middle line:84%
NOT A GREAT COMBINATION
IN YOUR LINE OF WORK.

00:07:25.780 --> 00:07:28.450 align:middle line:84%
DO YOU THINK VINCE
OR BILLY BERNARD WOULD--

00:07:28.450 --> 00:07:29.740 align:middle line:84%
THEY HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT, OKAY?

00:07:29.740 --> 00:07:33.100 align:middle line:90%
CRIME DOES NOT...

00:07:33.100 --> 00:07:37.420 align:middle line:90%
HAVE YOU GOT A QUARTER?

00:07:52.390 --> 00:07:54.810 align:middle line:90%
ALEX, IS THAT YOU?

00:07:54.810 --> 00:07:56.350 align:middle line:90%
NO, IT'S BRAD PITT.

00:07:57.390 --> 00:07:58.480 align:middle line:90%
OH, BRAD, YOU GOTTA GO.

00:07:58.480 --> 00:08:03.150 align:middle line:84%
UH, MY HUSBAND OR MY CRAZY SON
WILL BE HOME SOON.

00:08:04.360 --> 00:08:05.480 align:middle line:90%
HI, MOM. WHAT'S COOKING?

00:08:05.480 --> 00:08:07.570 align:middle line:84%
OH, BABY,
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR HEAD?

00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:09.450 align:middle line:84%
IT'S NOTHING,
JUST A SMALL ACCIDENT.

00:08:09.450 --> 00:08:10.240 align:middle line:84%
YEAH, WELL,
DOES IT HURT, THOUGH?

00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:12.070 align:middle line:84%
MAYBE I SHOULD
CLEAN IT BECAUSE--

00:08:12.070 --> 00:08:12.830 align:middle line:90%
MOM, MOM--

00:08:12.830 --> 00:08:13.410 align:middle line:84%
NO, INFECTIONS
CAN GET KIND OF--

00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:15.040 align:middle line:90%
MOM, STOP, STOP, IT'S FINE.

00:08:15.040 --> 00:08:16.910 align:middle line:84%
[SIGHS] YOU'VE JUST
GOT TO BE CAREFUL, OKAY?

00:08:16.910 --> 00:08:17.790 align:middle line:84%
I KNOW, BUT DAD CLEANED IT
EARLIER THIS MORNING.

00:08:17.790 --> 00:08:19.710 align:middle line:90%
IT'S OKAY.

00:08:19.710 --> 00:08:21.000 align:middle line:90%
OH...

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:23.590 align:middle line:84%
YOU GOT HURT WHILE YOU WERE
RUNNING, DIDN'T YOU?

00:08:23.590 --> 00:08:24.880 align:middle line:90%
[SCOFFS]

00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:27.170 align:middle line:84%
WAIT TILL I TALK
TO THAT MAN.

00:08:27.170 --> 00:08:28.630 align:middle line:84%
IF HE THINKS
BEING ON A DIET IS TOUGH--

00:08:28.630 --> 00:08:31.010 align:middle line:84%
I WAS THE ONE WHO'S AT FAULT,
IT'S NOT DAD'S FAULT.

00:08:31.010 --> 00:08:33.049 align:middle line:90%
ALL RIGHT?

00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:38.429 align:middle line:90%
DON'T GULP, PLEASE.

00:08:38.429 --> 00:08:39.600 align:middle line:90%
AND JUST USE A GLASS.

00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:41.520 align:middle line:90%
DID DAD CALL?

00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:43.150 align:middle line:90%
NO.

00:08:43.860 --> 00:08:46.730 align:middle line:84%
WHY? WHAT ARE
YOU TWO PLOTTING?

00:08:46.730 --> 00:08:48.900 align:middle line:90%
IT'S NOTHING.

00:08:51.950 --> 00:08:53.280 align:middle line:90%
OH, WATCH OUT.

00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:54.700 align:middle line:84%
I LEFT THE VACUUM
AT THE TOP OF THE STAIRS, SORRY.

00:08:58.960 --> 00:09:03.790 align:middle line:90%


00:09:47.590 --> 00:09:49.510 align:middle line:90%
[KNOCKS] HI

00:09:49.510 --> 00:09:50.720 align:middle line:90%
GEOFF TAYLOR.

00:09:50.720 --> 00:09:52.010 align:middle line:84%
I'M NOT SURE IF YOU REMEMBER,
WE SPOKE ONCE ON THE PHONE.

00:09:52.010 --> 00:09:54.890 align:middle line:90%
YES, YOU'RE ALEX'S FATHER.

00:09:54.890 --> 00:09:55.220 align:middle line:90%
HE'S A VERY SWEET KID.

00:09:55.220 --> 00:09:57.180 align:middle line:90%
THANK YOU.

00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:58.970 align:middle line:84%
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT
HIM BEING ON CROSS COUNTRY TEAM.

00:09:58.970 --> 00:10:03.060 align:middle line:84%
OH, GEE, I'M SORRY, MR. TAYLOR.
WE'VE ALREADY STARTED TRAINING.

00:10:03.060 --> 00:10:04.690 align:middle line:84%
OUR FIRST RACE
IS VERY SOON.

00:10:04.690 --> 00:10:05.350 align:middle line:84%
WELL, YOU TOLD ME
YOU'D CALL ME

00:10:05.350 --> 00:10:08.320 align:middle line:84%
BEFORE YOU STARTED
TRAINING.

00:10:08.320 --> 00:10:10.780 align:middle line:90%
I'VE JUST BEEN REALLY BUSY...

00:10:10.780 --> 00:10:14.740 align:middle line:84%
WELL, THIS IS KIND OF
A SPECIAL CASE.

00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:18.660 align:middle line:84%
LOOK, IF HE'S
AS FAST AS YOU SAY HE IS,

00:10:18.660 --> 00:10:21.540 align:middle line:84%
I JUST DON'T REALLY HAVE ANYONE
TO RUN WITH HIM.

00:10:21.540 --> 00:10:25.170 align:middle line:84%
MY BEST RUNNERS, THEY'RE
TRAINING FOR THEIR OWN RACES.

00:10:25.170 --> 00:10:26.710 align:middle line:84%
SO, IF I FIND SOMEONE
TO RUN WITH HIM,

00:10:26.710 --> 00:10:28.090 align:middle line:90%
HE CAN BE ON THE TEAM?

00:10:28.090 --> 00:10:30.090 align:middle line:90%
I DIDN'T SAY THAT,

00:10:30.090 --> 00:10:33.220 align:middle line:84%
AND WE WOULD HAVE TO MEET
THE ENTRY

00:10:33.220 --> 00:10:35.630 align:middle line:84%
AND INSURANCE
CONSIDERATIONS, SO...

00:10:38.140 --> 00:10:39.720 align:middle line:90%
YEAH, I MEAN, I GUESS

00:10:39.720 --> 00:10:41.060 align:middle line:84%
IF YOU FOUND SOMEONE
FAST ENOUGH TO RUN WITH HIM,

00:10:41.060 --> 00:10:43.390 align:middle line:90%
WHO WENT TO THIS SCHOOL,

00:10:43.390 --> 00:10:45.900 align:middle line:84%
AND IS NOT ALREADY
ON THE CROSS COUNTRY TEAM,

00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:47.020 align:middle line:90%
HE COULD TRY OUT.

00:10:47.020 --> 00:10:49.650 align:middle line:90%
OKAY, THANKS.

00:10:49.940 --> 00:10:52.110 align:middle line:90%
TRY OUT!

00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:54.200 align:middle line:90%
THANK YOU.

00:10:54.200 --> 00:10:57.570 align:middle line:84%
I JUST DON'T LIKE IT
WHEN YOU GET HIS HOPES UP.

00:10:57.570 --> 00:10:58.910 align:middle line:84%
I'M NOT GETTING
ANYBODY'S HOPES UP,

00:10:58.910 --> 00:11:00.160 align:middle line:84%
HE'S GOING TO
MAKE THE TEAM.

00:11:01.870 --> 00:11:04.830 align:middle line:84%
I DON'T WANT TO
SEE HIM GET HURT.

00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:05.750 align:middle line:90%
HE'S NOT GOING TO GET HURT.

00:11:05.750 --> 00:11:06.750 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW,
YOU SAID THE SAME THING

00:11:06.750 --> 00:11:07.920 align:middle line:84%
WHEN HE WANTED TO GO
TO HIGH SCHOOL

00:11:07.920 --> 00:11:10.000 align:middle line:84%
WITHOUT A GUIDE DOG
OR AN ASSISTANT,

00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:12.590 align:middle line:84%
AND HE MEMORIZED THAT PLACE
JUST LIKE HE DID AT HOME,

00:11:12.590 --> 00:11:13.710 align:middle line:90%
AND HE'S FINE.

00:11:13.710 --> 00:11:16.130 align:middle line:84%
HE'S GOT JULIE
TO WATCH OUT FOR HIM THERE,

00:11:16.130 --> 00:11:17.340 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW, IT'S
COMPLETELY DIFFERENT.

00:11:17.340 --> 00:11:19.100 align:middle line:84%
LOOK, HE'S
GOING TO GET HURT.

00:11:19.100 --> 00:11:20.390 align:middle line:90%
HE'S NOT GOING TO GET HURT.

00:11:20.390 --> 00:11:23.930 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW WHAT, THESE ARE
THE KIDS WHO ARE HURT.

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:26.730 align:middle line:90%
GEOFF, ALL I'M SAYING

00:11:26.730 --> 00:11:27.900 align:middle line:84%
IS THAT I DON'T
THINK IT'S RIGHT

00:11:27.900 --> 00:11:29.730 align:middle line:84%
TO GIVE HIM DREAMS
OF COMPETING

00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:33.150 align:middle line:84%
IN SOME SPORT IN WHICH
HE CAN NEVER POSSIBLY WIN

00:11:33.150 --> 00:11:34.190 align:middle line:84%
AND THAT IS
SO DANGEROUS FOR HIM--

00:11:34.190 --> 00:11:35.530 align:middle line:90%
IF YOU HAD YOUR WAY,

00:11:35.530 --> 00:11:37.990 align:middle line:84%
WE'D BE WRAPPING HIM UP
IN BUBBLE WRAP ALL DAY.

00:11:37.990 --> 00:11:39.950 align:middle line:90%
[MUFFLED ARGUMENTS CONTINUE]

00:11:39.950 --> 00:11:40.950 align:middle line:90%
I WANT TO GIVE MY SON

00:11:40.950 --> 00:11:41.490 align:middle line:84%
EVERY OPPORTUNITY
IN LIFE I CAN,

00:11:41.490 --> 00:11:43.660 align:middle line:84%
TO SUCCEED
OR TO FAIL.

00:11:43.660 --> 00:11:45.200 align:middle line:84%
IF HE WANTS TO RUN
CROSS COUNTRY,

00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:46.830 align:middle line:84%
THAT'S WHAT HE'S
GOING TO DO,

00:11:46.830 --> 00:11:47.960 align:middle line:84%
HE'S GOING TO RUN
CROSS COUNTRY.

00:11:47.960 --> 00:11:49.830 align:middle line:84%
IF HE WANTS TO START
SKEET SHOOTING, THEN--

00:11:49.830 --> 00:11:51.840 align:middle line:84%
OKAY, AND WHO IS
GOING TO RUN WITH HIM?

00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:53.130 align:middle line:90%
YOU, MR. USAIN BOLT?

00:11:53.130 --> 00:11:54.630 align:middle line:84%
YOU CAN'T EVEN
KEEP UP WITH HIM NOW!

00:11:54.630 --> 00:11:56.630 align:middle line:90%
I HAVE A VERY CLEVER PLAN.

00:11:56.630 --> 00:11:59.220 align:middle line:84%
CAN WE JUST
DROP THIS, PLEASE?

00:11:59.220 --> 00:12:03.430 align:middle line:84%
NOW I'M WEAK
FROM HUNGER...

00:12:04.220 --> 00:12:08.060 align:middle line:90%
VANDALISM, SHOPLIFTING,

00:12:08.060 --> 00:12:10.270 align:middle line:90%
AND NOW THIS.

00:12:10.270 --> 00:12:13.070 align:middle line:84%
IT SEEMS LIKE THE POLICE
ARE ALWAYS CHASING YOU.

00:12:13.070 --> 00:12:14.650 align:middle line:84%
YOU LIKE TO RUN,
DON'T YOU, BRAD?

00:12:14.650 --> 00:12:17.150 align:middle line:90%
I'VE DONE ENOUGH.

00:12:17.150 --> 00:12:19.450 align:middle line:84%
FIRST ARREST,
OFFICER BURNS SAID

00:12:19.450 --> 00:12:21.950 align:middle line:84%
HE CHASED YOU ALL OVER TOWN
FOR 45 MINUTES.

00:12:21.950 --> 00:12:25.370 align:middle line:84%
YOU OUTRAN
THEIR FASTEST GUY.

00:12:25.370 --> 00:12:26.500 align:middle line:90%
I'M FAST.

00:12:26.500 --> 00:12:28.830 align:middle line:84%
YOU EVER BEEN
ON THE TRACK TEAM, BRAD?

00:12:30.170 --> 00:12:32.960 align:middle line:90%
I DON'T LIKE JOCKS.

00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:35.670 align:middle line:90%
HEY...

00:12:35.670 --> 00:12:38.340 align:middle line:84%
SAYS HERE
YOU GO TO MY SON'S SCHOOL.

00:12:38.340 --> 00:12:41.890 align:middle line:90%
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

00:12:43.140 --> 00:12:45.060 align:middle line:90%
YEAH.

00:12:45.060 --> 00:12:46.970 align:middle line:90%
I'VE SEEN HIM AROUND.

00:12:46.970 --> 00:12:47.480 align:middle line:90%
HE'S, LIKE, BLIND, RIGHT?

00:12:47.480 --> 00:12:51.020 align:middle line:90%
THAT EXPLAINS A LOT.

00:12:51.020 --> 00:12:52.350 align:middle line:90%
HMM.

00:12:52.350 --> 00:12:55.770 align:middle line:90%
HE'S ALSO A REALLY COOL KID.

00:12:55.770 --> 00:12:58.190 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW,
JUDGE MELANSON WARNED YOU

00:12:58.190 --> 00:12:59.490 align:middle line:90%
ABOUT WHAT WOULD HAPPEN

00:12:59.490 --> 00:13:03.780 align:middle line:84%
IF YOU EVER SHOWED UP
IN HIS COURTROOM AGAIN.

00:13:03.780 --> 00:13:04.870 align:middle line:90%
I THINK I...

00:13:04.870 --> 00:13:07.870 align:middle line:84%
I THINK I HAVE AN IDEA
ABOUT HOW TO WORK THIS OUT.

00:13:07.870 --> 00:13:10.710 align:middle line:90%
YEAH?

00:13:10.710 --> 00:13:12.880 align:middle line:84%
WELL, I'M NOT
GOING TO RAT OUT ANYONE.

00:13:12.880 --> 00:13:15.380 align:middle line:84%
I MEAN, GO AHEAD, SEND ME
TO RIDGEMONT, I DON'T CARE.

00:13:15.380 --> 00:13:17.840 align:middle line:84%
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT THAT, THIS
IS SOMETHING ELSE.

00:13:17.840 --> 00:13:22.720 align:middle line:84%
I'D HAVE TO TALK TO YOUR FATHER
AND YOUR ATTORNEY FIRST.

00:13:22.720 --> 00:13:25.390 align:middle line:90%
MY FATHER DOESN'T CARE, SO...

00:13:25.390 --> 00:13:28.350 align:middle line:90%
I THINK HE DOES.

00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:29.980 align:middle line:84%
WHY ELSE WOULD HE
TAKE A DAY OFF FROM WORK

00:13:29.980 --> 00:13:31.440 align:middle line:90%
TO SHOW UP HERE?

00:13:35.020 --> 00:13:35.900 align:middle line:90%
MY FATHER'S HERE?

00:13:35.900 --> 00:13:37.730 align:middle line:84%
YEAH, DOWN IN THE COURTROOM
RIGHT NOW,

00:13:37.730 --> 00:13:39.570 align:middle line:84%
MAKING ALL
THE SECURITY GUARDS NERVOUS.

00:13:39.570 --> 00:13:42.400 align:middle line:84%
AND I'D HAVE TO TALK
TO THE JUDGE,

00:13:42.400 --> 00:13:46.330 align:middle line:84%
AND, HOPEFULLY, MELANSON'S
BACK ON HIS BRAN DIET.

00:13:46.330 --> 00:13:48.740 align:middle line:90%
BUT I THINK I CAN WORK IT OUT

00:13:48.740 --> 00:13:51.710 align:middle line:84%
SO YOU COULD STAY AT HOME
AND GO TO SCHOOL.

00:13:51.710 --> 00:13:52.750 align:middle line:90%
BUT THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT,

00:13:52.750 --> 00:13:55.000 align:middle line:90%
ISN'T IT, BRAD?

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.380 align:middle line:84%
SO, MY DAD SAID
I COULD COME HOME?

00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:00.920 align:middle line:90%
MM-HMM.

00:14:01.420 --> 00:14:03.180 align:middle line:90%
AND WHAT'S THE DEAL?

00:14:03.180 --> 00:14:04.970 align:middle line:90%
THE DEAL?

00:14:06.220 --> 00:14:08.680 align:middle line:90%
HERE'S THE DEAL, BRAD.

00:14:08.680 --> 00:14:10.850 align:middle line:84%
YOU KEEP YOUR NOSE CLEAN
FOR REAL THIS TIME

00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.100 align:middle line:90%
AND YOU ANSWER

00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:15.020 align:middle line:90%
ONE QUESTION,

00:14:15.020 --> 00:14:18.730 align:middle line:90%
CAN YOU, OR CAN YOU NOT, RUN?

00:14:21.030 --> 00:14:22.950 align:middle line:90%
BRAD COLEMAN?

00:14:22.950 --> 00:14:25.740 align:middle line:84%
YOU'RE GETTING BRAD COLEMAN
TO RUN WITH ME?

00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:25.950 align:middle line:84%
OH, I TAKE IT
YOU KNOW BRAD?

00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:29.410 align:middle line:84%
UM, EVERYBODY AT SCHOOL
KNOWS BRAD.

00:14:29.410 --> 00:14:30.240 align:middle line:90%
HE BEAT UP MS. McVIE.

00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:31.750 align:middle line:84%
YOU WANT ME TO
GO OUT FOR A SCHOOL TEAM

00:14:31.750 --> 00:14:33.500 align:middle line:84%
WITH THE GUY WHO BEAT UP
THE TRACK COACH?

00:14:33.500 --> 00:14:37.290 align:middle line:84%
TANYA McVIE?
SHE'S THE COACH?

00:14:37.290 --> 00:14:38.290 align:middle line:90%
YEAH.

00:14:38.290 --> 00:14:40.000 align:middle line:84%
IT SEEMS LIKE YESTERDAY
SHE WAS RUNNING TRACK,

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:42.010 align:middle line:84%
I REMEMBER SEEING HER PICTURE
IN THE PAPER ALL THE TIME.

00:14:42.010 --> 00:14:43.050 align:middle line:90%
SO YOU'RE GETTING A THUG

00:14:43.050 --> 00:14:45.010 align:middle line:90%
WHO ATTACKS TEACHERS,

00:14:45.010 --> 00:14:47.430 align:middle line:84%
YOUNG, SLIGHT,
VULNERABLE TEACHERS,

00:14:47.430 --> 00:14:48.180 align:middle line:84%
TO RUN WITH OUR SON,
OUR ONLY CHILD?

00:14:48.180 --> 00:14:50.680 align:middle line:90%
WAIT, "SLIGHT?"

00:14:50.680 --> 00:14:53.810 align:middle line:84%
JULIE SAID MS. McVIE
WAS PLUMP AND HOMELY.

00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:54.980 align:middle line:90%
I WOULDN'T SAY THAT.

00:14:54.980 --> 00:14:56.480 align:middle line:90%
YEAH, I'M SURE YOU WOULDN'T.

00:14:56.480 --> 00:14:57.350 align:middle line:84%
HE DIDN'T BEAT HER UP,
HE PUSHED HER.

00:14:57.350 --> 00:15:00.190 align:middle line:90%
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

00:15:00.190 --> 00:15:01.860 align:middle line:84%
THERE WAS A RUCKUS,
SHE FELL DOWN.

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:02.320 align:middle line:90%
THE STAIRS.

00:15:02.320 --> 00:15:04.740 align:middle line:90%
I DON'T EVEN THINK

00:15:04.740 --> 00:15:05.150 align:middle line:84%
BRAD GOT SUSPENDED
THAT TIME.

00:15:05.150 --> 00:15:07.030 align:middle line:90%
THAT TIME?

00:15:07.030 --> 00:15:09.950 align:middle line:84%
AND I DON'T THINK MS. McVIE
WOULD EVEN REMEMBER IT.

00:15:09.950 --> 00:15:12.700 align:middle line:84%
HE ONCE GAVE HARLAN GLIEBERMAN
SUCH A BAD WEDGIE,

00:15:12.700 --> 00:15:14.100 align:middle line:84%
THAT HE WALKED LIKE
A DUCK FOR TWO WEEKS.

00:15:14.100 --> 00:15:17.330 align:middle line:84%
HARLAN GLIEBERMAN HAS
ALWAYS WALKED LIKE A DUCK.

00:15:17.330 --> 00:15:19.170 align:middle line:90%
SANDY...

00:15:19.170 --> 00:15:20.460 align:middle line:90%
BRAD'S MESSED UP,

00:15:20.460 --> 00:15:21.960 align:middle line:84%
BUT I THINK,
SOMETHING LIKE THIS,

00:15:21.960 --> 00:15:23.340 align:middle line:90%
FOR HIM TO FOCUS ON,

00:15:23.340 --> 00:15:24.590 align:middle line:84%
IT COULD REALLY HELP HIM
PULL IT TOGETHER.

00:15:26.090 --> 00:15:28.430 align:middle line:90%
ALEX, HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT IT?

00:15:28.430 --> 00:15:30.510 align:middle line:84%
HOW BADLY DO YOU
WANT TO MAKE THIS TEAM?

00:15:30.510 --> 00:15:34.480 align:middle line:84%
WHAT HAPPENS TO HIM
IF WE DON'T DO THIS?

00:15:34.480 --> 00:15:36.350 align:middle line:90%
HE'S GOING TO GO AWAY.

00:15:36.350 --> 00:15:40.230 align:middle line:90%
TO RIDGEMONT.

00:15:40.230 --> 00:15:42.940 align:middle line:84%
IT'S THE TOUGHEST FACILITY
IN THIS ENTIRE AREA.

00:15:42.940 --> 00:15:46.610 align:middle line:84%
THAT IS NOT GOING TO BE
A VACATION FOR BRAD.

00:15:46.610 --> 00:15:51.160 align:middle line:84%
BUT BRAD COLEMAN
IS OUT OF OPTIONS.

00:15:51.160 --> 00:15:54.240 align:middle line:84%
THIS WAS A FAVOR FOR ME
FROM JUDGE MELANSON, TOO.

00:15:54.240 --> 00:15:56.540 align:middle line:90%
WELL, CAN HE RUN?

00:15:56.540 --> 00:15:59.420 align:middle line:84%
THE COPS SAY
HE CAN RUN REALLY FAST.

00:15:59.420 --> 00:16:02.040 align:middle line:84%
WELL, WHAT DOES BRAD SAY
ABOUT THIS WHOLE PLAN ANYWAY?

00:16:02.040 --> 00:16:02.960 align:middle line:84%
I THINK HE'S
LOOKING FORWARD TO IT.

00:16:05.800 --> 00:16:07.170 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW WHAT,
I CAN'T DO THIS.

00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:08.220 align:middle line:90%
I REALLY CAN'T

00:16:08.220 --> 00:16:10.220 align:middle line:84%
YOU'RE NOT
PUNKING OUT OF THIS.

00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:11.890 align:middle line:84%
YOU WANT TO GO
TO THE RIDGE?

00:16:11.890 --> 00:16:12.930 align:middle line:90%
DO YOU?

00:16:12.930 --> 00:16:13.760 align:middle line:90%
NO.

00:16:13.760 --> 00:16:15.970 align:middle line:84%
THEN SHUT AND TAKE
YOUR MEDICINE.

00:16:17.890 --> 00:16:19.400 align:middle line:90%
[BROTHER GIGGLING]

00:16:19.400 --> 00:16:24.440 align:middle line:84%
ANY MORE OF THAT, RICKY,
AND YOU'RE WALKING.

00:16:24.440 --> 00:16:25.650 align:middle line:84%
NICE NEIGHBOURHOOD
YOUR COP FRIEND LIVES IN.

00:16:25.650 --> 00:16:30.160 align:middle line:84%
HE'S NOT A COP,
AND HE'S NOT MY FRIEND.

00:16:30.160 --> 00:16:32.570 align:middle line:84%
[RICKY]:
IS THAT THE COP?

00:16:32.570 --> 00:16:34.030 align:middle line:90%
HE AIN'T NO COP.

00:16:36.120 --> 00:16:38.330 align:middle line:84%
HEY, MR. COLEMAN.
HOW ARE YOU?

00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:40.500 align:middle line:90%
JUST PEACHY.

00:16:40.500 --> 00:16:43.840 align:middle line:90%
OOH, IT'S QUITE A RIG.

00:16:43.840 --> 00:16:46.460 align:middle line:84%
WHAT DO YOU GOT, UH,
16, 17...

00:16:46.460 --> 00:16:49.090 align:middle line:90%
18 CYLINDERS IN THIS THING--

00:16:49.090 --> 00:16:52.890 align:middle line:84%
LOOK, I, UH,
GOT STUFF I GOTTA DO.

00:17:03.060 --> 00:17:03.730 align:middle line:84%
MY DAD'S
A FUN GUY, HUH?

00:17:03.730 --> 00:17:07.109 align:middle line:84%
WELL, ONCE
YOU GET TO KNOW HIM.

00:17:07.109 --> 00:17:07.530 align:middle line:84%
YEAH, THAT'S WHEN
THE BIG LAUGHS

00:17:07.530 --> 00:17:09.490 align:middle line:90%
START TO HAPPEN.

00:17:09.490 --> 00:17:11.280 align:middle line:84%
LET'S GET THIS
OVER WITH.

00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:17.329 align:middle line:90%
ALEX... BRAD.

00:17:17.329 --> 00:17:20.079 align:middle line:84%
I'LL LET YOU GUYS
GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER.

00:17:21.290 --> 00:17:23.960 align:middle line:90%
HI.

00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:25.460 align:middle line:90%
HI!

00:17:25.460 --> 00:17:28.339 align:middle line:84%
I'M BLIND NOT DEAF,
YOU DON'T NEED TO YELL.

00:17:28.339 --> 00:17:30.800 align:middle line:90%
SORRY.

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:33.640 align:middle line:84%
IT'S ALL RIGHT,
IT HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.

00:17:33.640 --> 00:17:36.720 align:middle line:84%
YOU CAN TAKE A SEAT
IF YOU WANT.

00:17:40.020 --> 00:17:42.980 align:middle line:84%
OR... MAYBE I CAN SIGN
AN 8X10 GLOSSY

00:17:42.980 --> 00:17:47.320 align:middle line:84%
YOU CAN TAKE IT HOME
AND STARE AT IN PRIVATE.

00:17:47.320 --> 00:17:48.980 align:middle line:90%
YEAH... FUNNY.

00:17:55.410 --> 00:17:57.830 align:middle line:84%
YOU GUYS ARE
PRETTY LOADED, HUH?

00:17:57.830 --> 00:18:01.080 align:middle line:84%
THAT'S, LIKE, THE BIGGEST TV
I'VE EVER SEEN.

00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.170 align:middle line:90%
MUST BE COOL TO WATCH...

00:18:04.750 --> 00:18:05.710 align:middle line:90%
RIGHT...

00:18:12.550 --> 00:18:14.300 align:middle line:90%
BRAD?

00:18:14.300 --> 00:18:17.390 align:middle line:84%
I'M JUST LOOKING.
I'M NOT GOING TO STEAL YOUR TV.

00:18:17.390 --> 00:18:19.220 align:middle line:90%
GREAT.

00:18:19.220 --> 00:18:20.350 align:middle line:90%
THANK YOU.

00:18:20.350 --> 00:18:24.190 align:middle line:84%
I JUST WANTED TO KNOW IF
YOU WANTED SOMETHING TO DRINK.

00:18:24.190 --> 00:18:27.610 align:middle line:84%
AND THAT'S NOT MY TV,
THE CREDIT CARD COMPANY OWNS IT.

00:18:28.520 --> 00:18:31.150 align:middle line:90%
YEAH, I'M GOOD.

00:18:31.150 --> 00:18:31.190 align:middle line:90%
THANKS.

00:18:37.370 --> 00:18:44.210 align:middle line:84%
SO... IS IT, UH,
TOUGH BEING BLIND?

00:18:44.210 --> 00:18:47.540 align:middle line:84%
I MEAN, IS IT
TOUGH BEING YOU?

00:18:47.540 --> 00:18:49.630 align:middle line:84%
I'VE BEEN BLIND
SINCE I WAS TWO.

00:18:49.630 --> 00:18:52.380 align:middle line:84%
I REALLY DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING DIFFERENT.

00:18:52.380 --> 00:18:54.510 align:middle line:84%
BESIDES, I LIKE TO THINK
MY OTHER SENSES

00:18:54.510 --> 00:18:56.300 align:middle line:90%
MAKE UP FOR IT.

00:18:56.300 --> 00:18:57.140 align:middle line:84%
I ALSO HAVE
SUPERHUMAN STRENGTH

00:18:57.140 --> 00:19:01.430 align:middle line:84%
AND CAN SHOOT LASERS
FROM MY THUMBS.

00:19:01.430 --> 00:19:03.390 align:middle line:84%
AND AN OVERACTIVE
SARCASM GLAND,

00:19:03.390 --> 00:19:05.440 align:middle line:90%
LUCKY YOU.

00:19:05.440 --> 00:19:08.400 align:middle line:90%
I HAVE THAT, TOO, YEAH.

00:19:17.240 --> 00:19:19.370 align:middle line:84%
HOW ARE YOU GUYS
GETTING ALONG?

00:19:21.580 --> 00:19:24.290 align:middle line:90%
THAT WELL, HUH?

00:19:24.290 --> 00:19:26.710 align:middle line:84%
UH, BUB, WHY DON'T YOU
TELL YOUR MOM

00:19:26.710 --> 00:19:28.210 align:middle line:90%
YOU'RE GOING TO GO FOR A RUN?

00:19:28.210 --> 00:19:29.590 align:middle line:90%
YUP.

00:19:35.050 --> 00:19:36.130 align:middle line:90%
YOU TWO HITTING IT OFF?

00:19:36.130 --> 00:19:38.340 align:middle line:90%
HE HATES ME.

00:19:41.600 --> 00:19:44.270 align:middle line:90%
HOW DID IT GO?

00:19:44.270 --> 00:19:47.440 align:middle line:90%
HE HATES ME.

00:19:47.440 --> 00:19:49.730 align:middle line:90%
I'LL BRING THE CAR AROUND!

00:19:54.570 --> 00:19:58.660 align:middle line:90%


00:20:07.290 --> 00:20:09.290 align:middle line:90%
OKAY, LET'S GO.

00:20:09.290 --> 00:20:11.340 align:middle line:84%
WAIT, ACTUALLY,
YOU DON'T GRAB MY ARM.

00:20:11.340 --> 00:20:13.000 align:middle line:84%
IT'S A LITTLE HARD FOR ME
TO RUN THAT WAY.

00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:14.500 align:middle line:84%
OKAY, SO THIS WHOLE THING
IS ACTUALLY ABOUT US

00:20:14.500 --> 00:20:15.260 align:middle line:90%
FINDING A RHYTHM,

00:20:15.260 --> 00:20:18.260 align:middle line:84%
EVEN THINKING ALIKE
AFTER A WHILE.

00:20:18.260 --> 00:20:20.590 align:middle line:84%
YEAH, RIGHT, LIKE
THAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN.

00:20:20.590 --> 00:20:22.800 align:middle line:90%
OKAY, YOU READY?

00:20:22.800 --> 00:20:25.140 align:middle line:90%
UH... YEAH.

00:20:26.680 --> 00:20:29.230 align:middle line:90%


00:20:33.360 --> 00:20:34.150 align:middle line:84%
[BRAD]: OKAY, TELL ME
IF I'M GOING TOO FAST.

00:20:34.150 --> 00:20:37.150 align:middle line:84%
IT'S ACTUALLY
KIND OF SLOW RIGHT NOW.

00:20:37.150 --> 00:20:38.150 align:middle line:90%
YEAH?

00:20:38.150 --> 00:20:39.030 align:middle line:90%
THAT'S BETTER.

00:20:39.030 --> 00:20:40.200 align:middle line:84%
ALL RIGHT, CORNER
TO THE RIGHT COMING UP.

00:20:40.200 --> 00:20:41.240 align:middle line:90%
I KNOW.

00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:41.570 align:middle line:84%
DO YOU WANT ME
TO DO THIS OR NOT?

