00:29:11.790 --> 00:29:14.210 align:middle line:90%
COME ON, GUYS.

00:29:16.590 --> 00:29:18.800 align:middle line:90%
I'M NOT SCARED OF YOU, CHIEF.

00:29:20.260 --> 00:29:23.220 align:middle line:90%
YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

00:29:25.760 --> 00:29:28.680 align:middle line:84%
UNLIKE YOU,
I HAVE A REASON TO BE HERE.

00:29:28.680 --> 00:29:30.890 align:middle line:84%
YOU GUYS ALMOST
READY IN THERE?

00:29:30.890 --> 00:29:33.060 align:middle line:90%
UH, YEAH, WE'RE COOL.

00:29:41.910 --> 00:29:42.160 align:middle line:90%
YOU READY?

00:29:42.160 --> 00:29:43.780 align:middle line:90%
YEAH.

00:29:52.790 --> 00:29:54.250 align:middle line:90%
HEY, COACH.

00:30:16.650 --> 00:30:17.070 align:middle line:84%
BRADLEY, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:30:17.070 --> 00:30:19.360 align:middle line:90%
I'M STRETCHING.

00:30:19.360 --> 00:30:20.690 align:middle line:84%
WE CAN'T HAVE
ANY TROUBLE HERE.

00:30:20.690 --> 00:30:22.700 align:middle line:84%
THESE BOYS HAVE WORKED
VERY HARD TO GET THIS FAR.

00:30:22.700 --> 00:30:23.910 align:middle line:84%
THERE WON'T BE
ANY TROUBLE.

00:30:23.910 --> 00:30:25.370 align:middle line:84%
WELL, YOU AND I HAVE
A HISTORY, COLEMAN,

00:30:25.370 --> 00:30:27.080 align:middle line:90%
AND IT ISN'T GOOD.

00:30:27.080 --> 00:30:29.410 align:middle line:84%
YOU DON'T SEEM
TO APPRECIATE RULES.

00:30:29.410 --> 00:30:31.540 align:middle line:84%
IF I HAD KNOWN THAT IT WAS YOU,
THIS WOULDN'T HAVE HAPPENED.

00:30:31.540 --> 00:30:33.370 align:middle line:84%
STRINGS WERE PULLED
FOR ALEX, NOT FOR YOU,

00:30:33.370 --> 00:30:35.880 align:middle line:90%
AND I CAN END THIS ALL

00:30:35.880 --> 00:30:38.630 align:middle line:90%
AT ANY TIME.

00:30:38.630 --> 00:30:41.050 align:middle line:84%
JUST DON'T LET
YOUR FRIEND DOWN.

00:30:41.050 --> 00:30:41.920 align:middle line:90%
HE'S NOT MY FRIEND.

00:30:41.920 --> 00:30:44.130 align:middle line:90%
YEAH, WELL, I'M NOT SURPRISED.

00:30:44.130 --> 00:30:46.050 align:middle line:90%
THE THINNEST OF ICE, MISTER.

00:30:46.050 --> 00:30:47.930 align:middle line:90%
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

00:30:47.930 --> 00:30:48.390 align:middle line:90%
I KNOW THE ROUTINE.

00:30:48.390 --> 00:30:50.970 align:middle line:90%
[WHISTLE BLASTING]

00:30:51.430 --> 00:30:53.770 align:middle line:90%
[CLEARING THROAT]

00:30:53.770 --> 00:30:56.020 align:middle line:84%
THE REGULAR ROUTE, GUYS,
INTO THE BUSH TRAIL.

00:30:56.020 --> 00:30:57.400 align:middle line:84%
TYSON'S GOING TO
LEAD THE WAY.

00:30:57.400 --> 00:30:59.520 align:middle line:84%
ALL RIGHT,
CATCH ME IF YOU CAN.

00:31:01.400 --> 00:31:04.110 align:middle line:90%
LET'S GO.

00:31:04.110 --> 00:31:05.820 align:middle line:84%
OKAY, THAT'S THE ROUTE
THEY USE HERE

00:31:05.820 --> 00:31:07.280 align:middle line:90%
DURING A MEET.

00:31:07.280 --> 00:31:08.070 align:middle line:84%
YEAH? STAY CLOSE,
IT GETS NARROW.

00:31:08.070 --> 00:31:11.450 align:middle line:84%
HEY, IS MS. McVIE
FAT AND UGLY?

00:31:11.450 --> 00:31:13.080 align:middle line:84%
NO, I MEAN, SHE'S
MEAN AND EVERYTHING,

00:31:13.080 --> 00:31:14.210 align:middle line:84%
BUT SHE'S ACTUALLY
PRETTY HOT.

00:31:14.210 --> 00:31:17.500 align:middle line:84%
WHY DO YOU THINK SO MANY GUYS
ARE TRYING OUT FOR THE TEAM?

00:31:19.880 --> 00:31:21.460 align:middle line:90%


00:31:37.310 --> 00:31:39.480 align:middle line:90%
WHOA, EASY, GUYS.

00:31:39.480 --> 00:31:41.320 align:middle line:84%
YOU TRYING TO MAKE
TURBO TYSON LOOK BAD?

00:31:51.490 --> 00:31:53.160 align:middle line:84%
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE COMING UP
ON THE BIG HERO.

00:31:53.160 --> 00:31:54.790 align:middle line:90%
GOOD.

00:32:03.170 --> 00:32:05.170 align:middle line:90%
HE'S GOING FASTER.

00:32:05.170 --> 00:32:07.010 align:middle line:84%
NOT FAST ENOUGH.
WE CAN CATCH HIM.

00:32:07.010 --> 00:32:09.050 align:middle line:90%
NO...

00:32:09.050 --> 00:32:10.470 align:middle line:90%
NO, WE CAN'T.

00:32:10.470 --> 00:32:11.510 align:middle line:84%
HE'S CHUGGING
LIKE A FREIGHT TRAIN--

00:32:11.510 --> 00:32:12.850 align:middle line:90%
WE CAN PASS HIM.

00:32:12.850 --> 00:32:13.850 align:middle line:90%
I SAID NO, OKAY?

00:32:13.850 --> 00:32:15.980 align:middle line:90%
COME ON, WE CAN'T.

00:32:17.810 --> 00:32:19.020 align:middle line:84%
[TYSON CHEERS]
WHOO!

00:32:19.020 --> 00:32:20.190 align:middle line:90%
YEAH, BABY!

00:32:20.190 --> 00:32:21.400 align:middle line:90%
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, HUH?

00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:22.900 align:middle line:90%
WHY DIDN'T WE PASS HIM?

00:32:22.900 --> 00:32:24.070 align:middle line:90%
JUST LET IT GO, OKAY?

00:32:24.980 --> 00:32:26.820 align:middle line:90%
NO, NO, WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

00:32:26.820 --> 00:32:28.070 align:middle line:90%
ARE YOU SCARED OF HIM?

00:32:28.070 --> 00:32:28.610 align:middle line:90%
I SAID, DROP IT, OKAY?

00:32:28.610 --> 00:32:31.870 align:middle line:84%
A PROBLEM
HERE, GUYS?

00:32:31.870 --> 00:32:33.330 align:middle line:90%
WELL?

00:32:33.330 --> 00:32:34.830 align:middle line:90%
THERE'S NO PROBLEM, COACH.

00:32:34.830 --> 00:32:36.410 align:middle line:84%
WE WERE JUST, UH,
DISCUSSING STRATEGY.

00:32:36.410 --> 00:32:39.540 align:middle line:84%
HMM. I DIDN'T
EVEN KNOW

00:32:39.540 --> 00:32:41.210 align:middle line:84%
YOU COULD SPELL
"STRATEGY" COLEMAN.

00:32:41.210 --> 00:32:45.960 align:middle line:84%
YEAH, IT'S WITH
AND "F" AND A "U", RIGHT?

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:47.300 align:middle line:84%
ALEX, THERE'S ANOTHER
PRACTICE TOMORROW.

00:32:47.300 --> 00:32:49.090 align:middle line:90%
[SIGHS]

00:32:49.090 --> 00:32:50.300 align:middle line:90%
YEAH?

00:32:50.300 --> 00:32:52.850 align:middle line:84%
YOU GOING TO
BE THERE, BRAD?

00:32:52.850 --> 00:32:54.100 align:middle line:84%
I DON'T KNOW,
DO YOU WANT ME TO BE?

00:32:54.100 --> 00:32:56.430 align:middle line:90%
NO.

00:32:56.430 --> 00:32:59.480 align:middle line:84%
THEN, YEAH,
I'LL BE THERE.

00:33:06.440 --> 00:33:08.950 align:middle line:84%
SO, YOU HAVEN'T
TOLD US YET,

00:33:08.950 --> 00:33:10.320 align:middle line:90%
HOW DID IT GO TODAY?

00:33:10.320 --> 00:33:11.990 align:middle line:90%
HOW DID WHAT GO?

00:33:11.990 --> 00:33:13.570 align:middle line:90%
THE PRACTICE.

00:33:13.570 --> 00:33:14.580 align:middle line:84%
HE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
THE ENTIRE RIDE HOME.

00:33:14.580 --> 00:33:18.080 align:middle line:84%
WHAT DID
MS. McVIE SAY?

00:33:18.080 --> 00:33:20.540 align:middle line:90%
I'M ON THE TEAM, I GUESS.

00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:22.040 align:middle line:84%
[DROPS CUTLERY]
YOU MADE--

00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:23.460 align:middle line:84%
THAT'S GREAT!
WE KNEW YOU COULD DO IT.

00:33:23.460 --> 00:33:25.340 align:middle line:90%
BUT... UH...

00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:28.590 align:middle line:90%
WHAT'S WRONG?

00:33:28.590 --> 00:33:30.220 align:middle line:90%
MAY I BE EXCUSED?

00:33:30.220 --> 00:33:33.180 align:middle line:84%
I'M JUST, I'M A LITTLE FULL,
THAT'S ALL.

00:33:34.300 --> 00:33:34.760 align:middle line:90%
IT'S BRAD, ISN'T IT?

00:33:34.760 --> 00:33:36.560 align:middle line:90%
HE'S HARASSING YOU.

00:33:36.560 --> 00:33:39.520 align:middle line:84%
I JUST HAVE A LOT OF HOMEWORK
TO DO, MOM, THAT'S IT.

00:33:39.520 --> 00:33:42.440 align:middle line:84%
DID HE PULL
ON YOUR UNDERWEAR?

00:33:45.270 --> 00:33:48.320 align:middle line:84%
HE'S PROBABLY JUST IN SHOCK,
IT IS PRETTY EXCITING.

00:33:48.320 --> 00:33:49.070 align:middle line:84%
I KNEW HE COULD DO IT
THE ENTIRE TIME.

00:34:02.960 --> 00:34:07.380 align:middle line:90%
SO WHAT'S WITH THE EYE?

00:34:07.380 --> 00:34:09.670 align:middle line:84%
NOTHING, JUST FELL
DURING PRACTICE.

00:34:09.670 --> 00:34:12.469 align:middle line:84%
SO NOT BERNARD BOYS
RELATED AT ALL?

00:34:12.469 --> 00:34:13.889 align:middle line:90%
NOPE.

00:34:13.889 --> 00:34:15.510 align:middle line:84%
I DON'T EVEN HANG OUT
WITH THEM ANYMORE.

00:34:15.510 --> 00:34:17.560 align:middle line:90%
YOU GOT ME WORRIED.

00:34:17.560 --> 00:34:19.310 align:middle line:90%
YOU'RE EATING.

00:34:22.310 --> 00:34:24.310 align:middle line:90%
I'M FINE.

00:34:25.690 --> 00:34:27.360 align:middle line:90%
YOU GOOD?

00:34:27.360 --> 00:34:28.150 align:middle line:90%
GOOD ENOUGH.

00:34:31.989 --> 00:34:33.570 align:middle line:84%
YOU'VE BEEN
PRETTY QUIET LATELY.

00:34:34.320 --> 00:34:35.659 align:middle line:90%
I'VE BEEN BUSY.

00:34:35.659 --> 00:34:40.080 align:middle line:84%
HEY, UH, DO WE HAVE
ANY MILK?

00:34:40.080 --> 00:34:42.290 align:middle line:90%
MILK?

00:34:42.290 --> 00:34:43.460 align:middle line:90%
YEAH, MILK.

00:34:43.460 --> 00:34:44.580 align:middle line:90%
YOU KNOW, WHITE STUFF.

00:34:44.580 --> 00:34:45.080 align:middle line:90%
IT COMES FROM A COW.

00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:49.460 align:middle line:90%
I AM FAMILIAR WITH THE CONCEPT.

00:34:49.460 --> 00:34:52.510 align:middle line:90%
YOU WANT MILK?

00:34:52.510 --> 00:34:54.300 align:middle line:90%
REALLY?

00:34:56.639 --> 00:34:59.810 align:middle line:90%
I'LL GET SOME TOMORROW.

00:35:00.810 --> 00:35:03.640 align:middle line:84%
SO, HOW'S
THE RUNNING GOING?

00:35:03.640 --> 00:35:04.520 align:middle line:90%
OKAY.

00:35:04.520 --> 00:35:05.770 align:middle line:90%
MUST BE OKAY,

00:35:05.770 --> 00:35:07.480 align:middle line:84%
I HAVEN'T GOT
ANY PHONE CALLS YET.

00:35:07.480 --> 00:35:09.400 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:35:10.020 --> 00:35:11.530 align:middle line:90%
I THOUGHT YOU LIKED TO RUN.

00:35:11.530 --> 00:35:15.360 align:middle line:90%
I DO, I GUESS.

00:35:15.360 --> 00:35:16.610 align:middle line:90%
AH,

00:35:16.610 --> 00:35:19.330 align:middle line:84%
YOU'RE NOT GETTING ALONG
WITH THAT BLIND KID, HUH?

00:35:19.330 --> 00:35:21.240 align:middle line:90%
HIS NAME'S ALEX.

00:35:21.240 --> 00:35:22.790 align:middle line:90%
AND I DON'T THINK HE LIKES ME.

00:35:22.790 --> 00:35:25.500 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW, HE'S ONE OF
THOSE RICH,

00:35:25.500 --> 00:35:27.380 align:middle line:90%
SMART KIDS.

00:35:27.380 --> 00:35:31.380 align:middle line:84%
OH, AND YOU'RE ONE OF
THE POOR, STUPID ONES?

00:35:31.380 --> 00:35:35.050 align:middle line:90%
I COME BY IT HONESTLY.

00:35:36.680 --> 00:35:37.760 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:35:41.060 --> 00:35:44.060 align:middle line:90%
DON'T GIVE UP YET.

00:35:44.060 --> 00:35:45.600 align:middle line:90%
IT MIGHT WORK OUT.

00:35:45.600 --> 00:35:47.400 align:middle line:90%
SOMETIMES, I THINK

00:35:47.400 --> 00:35:48.150 align:middle line:84%
WE GIVE UP
ON THINGS TOO QUICK.

00:35:51.480 --> 00:35:54.570 align:middle line:90%
BRAD...

00:35:54.570 --> 00:35:57.070 align:middle line:84%
I-- [CAR HONKS
IMPATIENTLY OUTSIDE]

00:36:00.370 --> 00:36:01.490 align:middle line:90%
I THOUGHT YOU SAID

00:36:01.490 --> 00:36:04.250 align:middle line:84%
YOU WEREN'T HANGING OUT
WITH VINCE AND BILLY ANYMORE?

00:36:04.250 --> 00:36:05.330 align:middle line:90%
I'M NOT.

00:36:05.330 --> 00:36:06.580 align:middle line:84%
THEN WHAT ARE THOSE
TWO DRAINS ON THE SYSTEM DOING

00:36:06.580 --> 00:36:08.580 align:middle line:90%
ON MY FRONT LAWN?

00:36:08.580 --> 00:36:10.630 align:middle line:84%
YO, BRAD, MAN, I'M
BORROWING YOUR JACKET.

00:36:10.630 --> 00:36:11.420 align:middle line:84%
HEY, WHERE THE HELL
ARE YOU GOING?

00:36:11.420 --> 00:36:14.130 align:middle line:84%
SEE YA! LOVE YOU!
HAVE A NICE DAY!

00:36:16.510 --> 00:36:17.050 align:middle line:84%
-HEY, MAN?
-WHAT'S UP, MAN?

00:36:17.050 --> 00:36:20.550 align:middle line:90%
[CAR ENGINE CHUGGING]

00:36:20.550 --> 00:36:22.640 align:middle line:90%
[CAR ROARS AWAY]

00:36:25.770 --> 00:36:30.100 align:middle line:90%


00:36:30.100 --> 00:36:31.060 align:middle line:90%
HELLO, GENTLEMEN.

00:36:31.060 --> 00:36:32.360 align:middle line:84%
I WOULD LIKE TO
SPEAK WITH YOU.

00:36:32.360 --> 00:36:34.440 align:middle line:90%
OKAY, SURE.

00:36:34.440 --> 00:36:35.150 align:middle line:84%
OUR FIRST MEET
IS TOMORROW,

00:36:35.150 --> 00:36:37.280 align:middle line:84%
AND IT'S A SHAME
THAT YOU TWO

00:36:37.280 --> 00:36:38.610 align:middle line:84%
HAVEN'T HAD TIME
TO WORK OUT WITH US

00:36:38.610 --> 00:36:39.610 align:middle line:90%
FROM THE BEGINNING.

00:36:39.610 --> 00:36:42.410 align:middle line:84%
I KNOW THAT WE HAVE
A LOT OF WORK TO DO, COACH--

00:36:42.410 --> 00:36:43.780 align:middle line:90%
SAVE IT, ALEX.

00:36:43.780 --> 00:36:46.790 align:middle line:84%
SHE'S SAYING
SHE DOESN'T WANT US TO GO.

00:36:46.790 --> 00:36:49.210 align:middle line:84%
YOU GOT IT ALL
FIGURED OUT, HUH, BRADLEY?

00:36:49.210 --> 00:36:50.710 align:middle line:84%
WHAT I WAS TRYING
TO TELL YOU

00:36:50.710 --> 00:36:53.040 align:middle line:84%
IS THAT NOT ONLY
CAN YOU RACE TOMORROW,

00:36:53.040 --> 00:36:54.630 align:middle line:84%
BUT YOU COULD DO
VERY WELL.

00:36:54.630 --> 00:36:55.760 align:middle line:90%
WAIT, REALLY?

00:36:55.760 --> 00:36:59.630 align:middle line:84%
SO, WE'RE GOING
TO THE MEET?

00:36:59.630 --> 00:37:00.800 align:middle line:90%
YES, BRADLEY,

00:37:00.800 --> 00:37:01.970 align:middle line:90%
YOU HAVE TIME OFF SCHOOL,

00:37:01.970 --> 00:37:04.310 align:middle line:84%
AND YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE TO
SHOVE ANYONE DOWN THE STAIRS.

00:37:07.480 --> 00:37:09.230 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:37:18.650 --> 00:37:21.610 align:middle line:84%
CAN YOU STOP
DOING THAT?

00:37:21.610 --> 00:37:23.320 align:middle line:90%
DOING WHAT?

00:37:23.320 --> 00:37:24.450 align:middle line:84%
THAT THING
WITH YOUR FINGERS.

00:37:24.450 --> 00:37:26.700 align:middle line:90%
SORRY.

00:37:26.700 --> 00:37:27.790 align:middle line:90%
JUST NERVOUS, I GUESS.

00:37:27.790 --> 00:37:30.250 align:middle line:90%
YOU?

00:37:30.250 --> 00:37:30.540 align:middle line:90%
NO.

00:37:30.540 --> 00:37:33.290 align:middle line:90%
LUCKY.

00:37:33.290 --> 00:37:34.540 align:middle line:84%
MY PARENTS ARE GOING
TO THE MEET TODAY.

00:37:34.540 --> 00:37:36.380 align:middle line:90%
ARE YOURS?

00:37:36.380 --> 00:37:38.840 align:middle line:90%
ANGUS IS WORKING.

00:37:38.840 --> 00:37:39.590 align:middle line:90%
WHAT DOES HE DO?

00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:41.340 align:middle line:90%
LINGERIE MODEL.

00:37:44.510 --> 00:37:46.310 align:middle line:90%
I'M JOKING.

00:37:46.310 --> 00:37:46.850 align:middle line:90%
I KNOW.

00:37:46.850 --> 00:37:50.180 align:middle line:90%
WHAT ABOUT YOUR MOTHER?

00:37:50.180 --> 00:37:53.650 align:middle line:84%
I DON'T-I DON'T
HAVE A MOTHER.

00:37:53.650 --> 00:37:55.940 align:middle line:90%
OH.

00:37:58.400 --> 00:37:59.860 align:middle line:90%
HEY, BRAD?

00:37:59.860 --> 00:38:01.740 align:middle line:90%
YEAH?

00:38:01.740 --> 00:38:03.410 align:middle line:84%
I WANT TO HAVE
THE WINDOW SEAT

00:38:03.410 --> 00:38:05.370 align:middle line:90%
ON THE RIDE BACK, OKAY?

00:38:05.370 --> 00:38:08.370 align:middle line:90%
OKAY.

00:38:08.370 --> 00:38:10.790 align:middle line:90%
I WAS JOKING.

00:38:14.830 --> 00:38:16.880 align:middle line:90%
I KNOW.

00:38:24.340 --> 00:38:26.180 align:middle line:90%


00:38:41.190 --> 00:38:42.240 align:middle line:90%
[STARTER PISTOL CRACKS]

00:38:47.580 --> 00:38:48.660 align:middle line:84%
HEY, HOW'S
IT GOING COACH?

00:38:48.660 --> 00:38:50.580 align:middle line:90%
GOOD.

00:38:50.580 --> 00:38:51.870 align:middle line:84%
A WEAK START,
BUT THEY'RE GAINING.

00:38:51.870 --> 00:38:52.460 align:middle line:84%
IF THEY CAN JUST
BE NEAR THE LEAD

00:38:52.460 --> 00:38:54.040 align:middle line:84%
GOING INTO
THE BUSH THERE,

00:38:54.040 --> 00:38:54.920 align:middle line:84%
THEY'RE GOING TO HAVE
A PRETTY GOOD CHANCE

00:38:54.920 --> 00:38:56.250 align:middle line:90%
OF FINISHING WELL.

00:38:56.250 --> 00:38:57.340 align:middle line:84%
THEY DO
A THREE-MILE LOOP

00:38:57.340 --> 00:38:59.380 align:middle line:84%
AND THEN THEY COME BACK
ACROSS THE MEADOW.

00:38:59.380 --> 00:39:01.300 align:middle line:84%
THAT'S IF TYSON
DOESN'T OVERTAKE THEM.

00:39:01.300 --> 00:39:01.760 align:middle line:84%
HE HAS KIND OF
A STRONG FINISHING KICK.

00:39:01.760 --> 00:39:03.380 align:middle line:90%
GO, ALEX! GO! GO!

00:39:05.430 --> 00:39:06.340 align:middle line:90%
[SANDY, ANXIOUS]: GEOFF, I--

00:39:06.340 --> 00:39:07.890 align:middle line:84%
YOU KNOW, THERE'S
SO MANY OF THEM.

00:39:07.890 --> 00:39:09.930 align:middle line:84%
I HAD NO IDEA THAT THERE
WOULD BE THIS MANY BOYS.

00:39:09.930 --> 00:39:10.850 align:middle line:84%
SOMETHING MIGHT
HAPPEN IN THERE.

00:39:10.850 --> 00:39:12.770 align:middle line:84%
OH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT IT...

00:39:12.770 --> 00:39:13.890 align:middle line:90%
NO, THREE MILES!

00:39:13.890 --> 00:39:15.690 align:middle line:84%
IT'S CROSS COUNTRY,
IT'S NOT FOOTBALL.

00:39:15.690 --> 00:39:17.440 align:middle line:90%
IT'S NOT A CONTACT SPORT.

00:39:22.400 --> 00:39:25.360 align:middle line:90%


00:39:36.960 --> 00:39:39.710 align:middle line:90%
WE COULD TAKE HIM.

00:39:39.710 --> 00:39:41.590 align:middle line:90%
LET'S DO IT.

00:39:43.590 --> 00:39:46.630 align:middle line:84%
THE PATH IS NARROW,
SO STAY CLOSE, OKAY?

00:39:50.140 --> 00:39:53.640 align:middle line:84%
THERE'S A ROOT
IN ONE, TWO, THREE...

00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:58.400 align:middle line:90%


00:40:09.410 --> 00:40:10.410 align:middle line:84%
HEY, STRETCH,
PULL OVER.

00:40:15.370 --> 00:40:16.910 align:middle line:84%
STAY OUT OF
MY WAY, HANDI!

